,"type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs. William Wynterheigh was born about 1343, in Dorset, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 2 sons with William Wynterheigh."},"et":{"abt 1343–":"umbes 1343–Surnud","1343–1424":"1343–1424","1377–1439":"1377–1439","1379–1429":"1379–1429","1343–Female":"1343–Surnud","1424":"1424","1379":"1379","1377":"1377","1343":"1343","ABT 1377":"umbes 1377","about 1379":"umbes 1379","1429":"1429","abt 1343":"umbes 1343","1439":"1439","of Chetnoll, Dorset, Eng.":"Dorset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","of,Chetnoll,Dorset,England":"Dorset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Dorset, England":"Dorset, England"},"fi":{"abt 1343–":"noin 1343–Kuollut","1343–1424":"1343–1424","1377–1439":"1377–1439","1379–1429":"1379–1429","1343–Female":"1343–Kuollut","1424":"1424","1379":"1379","1377":"1377","1343":"1343","ABT 1377":"noin 1377","about 1379":"noin 1379","1429":"1429","abt 1343":"noin 1343","1439":"1439","of Chetnoll, Dorset, Eng.":"Dorset, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","of,Chetnoll,Dorset,England":"Dorset, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Dorset, England":"Dorset, England"},"fr":{"abt 1343–":"environ 1343–Décédée","1343–1424":"1343–1424","1377–1439":"1377–1439","1379–1429":"1379–1429","1343–Female":"1343–Décédée","1424":"1424",